                            UCF’s Professional Master of Science in Real Estate (PMRE) is the Dr. P. Phillips School of Real Estate’s flagship program. It prepares students for senior-level positions in residential and commercial real estate brokerage, appraisal, development, and mortgage brokerage. Students continue their full-time careers while earning the accredited graduate degree.

                            Curriculum
PMRE classes meet Monday & Wednesday evenings, 6:00-9:50 p.m., at the Executive Development Center’s state-of-the-art downtown facility. The 30-credit hour curriculum comprises five sessions over 20 months. Core business courses in accounting, finance, and marketing will be offered with advanced coursework in residential and commercial real estate. Program graduates gain useful knowledge applicable to a variety of real estate-related fields.
